  "content": "Each document model has three key components:\n\n1. **State Schema** - Defines the structure of the document using GraphQL SDL (types, fields, scalars). This is the blueprint for data storage and validation.\n2. **Document Operations** - Defines how the document can be modified. Operations are specified as GraphQL `input` types and represent valid state transitions (e.g., `AddTodoItemInput`, `UpdateTodoItemInput`).\n3. **Event History** - An append-only log storing every operation applied to the document as a timestamped event.\n\nThe state schema acts as a template for document instances, operations act as commands, and the event history provides the complete audit trail.",
